 and remove from the heat. ","Preheat the oven to 160C/140C Fan/Gas 3.  ","To cook the fish, heat the oil in a large frying pan with an oven-proof handle. Carefully add the fish to the pan and cook over a medium heat. When the fish has browned on one side, turn it over. The best way is to turn the fish from the centre and keep either a fork or a spatula on top and a flat fish slice or spatula at the bottom.","When both sides of the fish are brown, place in the oven for 10-12 minutes until cooked through. ","Divide the fish between 4 plates and pour over the patia. Sprinkle the coriander on top and serve with steamed rice or warm chapattis."],"url":"www_bbc_co_uk_food_recipes_kolmi_ni_bharaei_34818","title":"Indian stuffed sea bass with a tomato patia","time":{"preparation":"30 mins to 1 hour","preparationMins":60,"cooking":"30 mins to 1 hour","cookingMins":60,"totalMins":120},"serves":"Serves 4","image":"https://food.files.bbci.co.uk/kandl-food/1911/images/bbc_placeholder.png","isVegetarian":false,"recommendations":0}
