ason with salt and pepper. Bake until crisp, then remove and leave to cool. Meanwhile cut 6 circles from the set jelly.","To serve, place 3 circles of jelly on a plate and top with the beef tartare and spiced tomatoes. Place the remaining jelly circles on top and spoon over the caviar. Dress the plate with the sourdough crisps, leaves and a drizzle of olive oil. "],"url":"www_bbc_co_uk_food_recipes_marinated_beef_tartare_10869","title":"Beef tartar, tomato jelly and sourdough crisps","time":{"preparation":"overnight","preparationMins":null,"cooking":"10 to 30 mins","cookingMins":30,"totalMins":30},"serves":"Serves 4","image":"https://food.files.bbci.co.uk/kandl-food/1911/images/bbc_placeholder.png","isVegetarian":false,"recommendations":0}
